3. cs.IT (Information Theory) - Submodular functions have also been studied in the context of information theory, particularly in the context of network coding and communication. 
4. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) - Submodular functions are a fundamental concept in discrete mathematics, and their maximization has been studied in various contexts such as combinatorial optimization and matroid theory.
